# Project Context

## What This Repo Is

AI-assisted assessment project: **Support Ticket Management System**.
Internal users create, update, comment on, search/filter, and progress tickets through a fixed lifecycle.

## Stack (do not substitute)

| Layer | Choice | Location |
|-------|--------|----------|
| Frontend | React + Vite + TypeScript | `src/frontend/` |
| Backend | FastAPI + SQLAlchemy + Alembic | `src/backend/` |
| Database | PostgreSQL | `database/` |
| Auth | JWT (login identifies `createdBy` for CSV export) | backend middleware + frontend protected routes |
| Tests | pytest + real PostgreSQL for integration tests | `tests/` |

## Domain Entities

- **User** — seeded + auth; fields: `id`, `name`, `email`, `role`
- **Ticket** — `id`, `title`, `description`, `priority`, `status`, `assignedTo`, `createdBy`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`
- **Comment** — `id`, `ticketId`, `message`, `createdBy`, `createdAt`

## Mandatory Core Behaviors

1. Ticket CRUD (list, detail, update fields + assignee)
2. Comments on tickets
3. Status changes **only** via state machine (see `state-machine.mdc`)
4. Backend validation; UI shows meaningful errors
5. Persistence survives restart
6. Search or filter on ticket list (at least one)
7. CSV export of **authenticated user's** self-created tickets (`createdBy` = current user)
8. Integration tests proving state-machine rules

## Code Placement

```
src/backend/app/routers/     # FastAPI route modules
src/backend/app/services/    # Business logic (state machine lives here)
src/backend/app/models/      # SQLAlchemy models
src/backend/app/schemas/     # Pydantic request/response
src/frontend/src/pages/      # Route-level views
src/frontend/src/components/ # Reusable UI
tests/backend/integration/   # Real-DB integration tests
```

## Do Not

- Add frameworks outside the stack above without explicit user approval
- Implement user-management CRUD UI (users are seeded; auth only)
- Bypass backend validation in the frontend
- Commit secrets (see `security-and-env.mdc`)
- Expand scope at the expense of lifecycle artifacts in repo root and `ai-prompts/`

